{"content": "I need to multiply 648 \u00d7 636 in base 9.\n\n**Step 1: Convert to base 10**\n- 648\u2089 = 6\u00d79\u00b2 + 4\u00d79\u00b9 + 8\u00d79\u2070 = 6\u00d781 + 4\u00d79 + 8\u00d71 = 486 + 36 + 8 = 530\u2081\u2080\n- 636\u2089 = 6\u00d79\u00b2 + 3\u00d79\u00b9 + 6\u00d79\u2070 = 6\u00d781 + 3\u00d79 + 6\u00d71 = 486 + 27 + 6 = 519\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 2: Multiply in base 10**\n- 530 \u00d7 519 = 275,070\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 3: Convert result to base 9**\n- 275070 \u00f7 9 = 30563 r 3\n- 30563 \u00f7 9 = 3395 r 8\n- 3395 \u00f7 9 = 377 r 2\n- 377 \u00f7 9 = 41 r 8\n- 41 \u00f7 9 = 4 r 5\n- 4 \u00f7 9 = 0 r 4\n\nReading from bottom to top: **458283\u2089**\n\n458283", "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5", "prompt_tokens": 827, "completion_tokens": 344}